The paper discusses the impact of edge cache and transport network on the performance of 5G wireless communication systems, which falls under the category of network infrastructure. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new performance metric that takes cost into account, which involves optimization and modeling, indicating the relevance of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the optimization of radio resource allocation, which falls under the category of control systems, indicating the relevance of cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the optimization of 5G systems for the Internet of Things (IoT), which falls under the category of multimedia, indicating the relevance of cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
